Parimal Marathe
*What are the types of waterproofing?*
The most common types of waterproofing are cementitious waterproofing, liquid waterproofing membrane, bituminous membrane, bituminous coating, and polyurethane liquid membrane.

Fibre Mesh With The thickness of 45GSM is Ideal for the waterproofing
waterproofing as designing the structure itself to be integrally waterproof and the primary resistance to water ingress.


Grade 1 says that some water seepage and damp areas may be tolerable and generally, this could refers to, as it says, car-parks and plant rooms. Even in these areas, the objective at the design stage is going to be to keep water out

Grade 2 No seepage is acceptable. Damp areas as a result of internal air moisture/condensation are tolerable; measures might be required to manage water vapour / condensation.

Grade 3 refers to and this is the objective for habitable buildings i.e. water ingress and damp areas are not acceptable. This means, that, aside from the waterproofing system, it is equally as important to consider the correct levels of heating, ventilation, air circulation, extraction

Civil Engineering MCQ Official 28.04.2023 19:05:43
IMPORTANT ğŸ“
Request to all SSC JE aspirants from side of @TeamMCQ

Important Message to SSC JE Aspirants
Request to all the SSC JE aspirants

1.Candidates already in BRO can skip BRO option while filling this year Preference form.

2.Candidates selected in MES in previous year can skip MES and BRO.

3.Candidates already in CWC can fill the dept, which they wish to go for (either CPWD or MES) and skip other departments.

4.Candidates who are expecting some better dept. either in SSC JE or in state Exams can skip the department which they are not truly willing to join.

5.Diploma candidates, who do not have the experience certificate and other documents required for Selection in depts like MES and BRO. kindly skip those dept while filling the form.

6.If the results of DDA JE is announced before the preference form of SSC JE / if the candidate is expecting to get selected in DDA JE. Kindly skip the depts/ quit preference form, if you are not willing to join any dept through SSC JE 2022 / Choose only the dept you want to join.

5.Requesting recently Selected candidates of State AE or JE to quit from the Further process(do not fill the Preference form) of SSC JE 2022 .This will give opportunity to other candidates to join their dream department.

6.Candidates who are not going to join any of the department through SSC JE 2022. Kindly do not fill the option form.

As we know preference form is the last stage of SSC JE 2022 - Final List of Selected candidates will be prepared by SSC, No additional candidates more than vacancy will not be there in the list this year.

Its a kind request from the SSC JE 2022 Aspirants.

Do not waste any Vacant Seats of any dept.
Already selected candidates think before you fill the form.
We may not expect such huge vacancies in SSC for engineers in the near future. This is very good opportunity for SSC JE aspirants to get into their dream dept .So requesting everyone to choose only the depts you prefer to join.
